    <para><emphasis role="bold">Description:</emphasis> Specifies the characterset (encoding, for example <userinput>UTF-8</userinput>) of messages using the legacy BSD-syslog protocol. To list the available character sets on a host, execute the <command>iconv -l</command> command. For details on how encoding affects the size of the message, see <xref linkend="message-size-and-encoding"/>.</para>
